{
  "texts": [
    "DL classifiers, specifically SpinalNet and CNN, utilised MRI scans from Kaggle and OASIS-3, while ML classifiers, including SVM, KNN, and XGBoost, leveraged gene microarray data from the NCBI database.",
    "By combining MRI and gene expression data, the authors created a multimodal diagnostic model for AD.",
    "LIME was integrated to provide interpretability, explaining the role of genes and ranking them based on probability values in AD prediction.",
    "In a similar study, Rahim et al. [107] introduced a multimodal deep-learning framework, combining a 3D CNN with a bidirectional recurrent neural network (BRNN).",
    "This framework captured intra-slice features from MRI volumes and identified inter-sequence patterns indicative of AD, utilising longitudinal data over a 6-month span."
  ]
}